decks.notes: The deck is focused on controlling the game through a combination of counterspells, removal spells, and card advantage. It seeks to disrupt the opponent's plans while building up its own resources to maintain control of the battlefield. With a wide range of counterspells like Counterspell, Force of Will, and Mana Leak, as well as removal spells like Fatal Push, Swords to Plowshares, and Toxic Deluge, the deck can handle a variety of threats. Additionally, card draw spells like Brainstorm, Ponder, and Search for Azcanta help to ensure a steady stream of resources. This deck aims to outlast the opponent and win through attrition by carefully managing its resources and interactions.

The main concept of this deck is to overwhelm the opponent with a mix of control and tempo plays using Lier, Disciple of the Drowned as the commander. The deck focuses on generating mana advantage with cards like High Tide and Extraplanar Lens to power out spells efficiently. It utilizes a wide range of cheap cantrips and counterspells to maintain card advantage and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The deck aims to quickly assemble a combo or lock pieces using cards like Brain Freeze and Turnabout, while also having the ability to protect its own strategy with counterspells like Force of Will and Pact of Negation. Overall, the deck aims to be proactive and efficient in its game plan, applying constant pressure on the opponent while maintaining control of the board.
